DATA[CrimsonPermanentAssurance]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Oswald belongs to the universe now.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/8TIkItj</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/wulotP0.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Oswald crossed the rainbow bridge yesterday. He passed at home peacefully after a day doing all his favorite things.  He was surrounded by love.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/mqiVGOS.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is from the first week I had Oswald.  He always looked a little worried like that.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/l9SjrJB.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Oswald was always a sweet and curmudgeonly sort. Never aggressive but mostly aloof.  We would joke that he was running cat software on dog hardware.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/q2jBN1M.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>We gave Ozzy his best last day.  He was a scavenger hound (as evinced by other postings I've made here) and so we hid slices of pizza in the bushes for him to find.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/WMpPlJE.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This was from earlier in the month when we took Ozzy to the beach, one of his favorite places. Ozzy walked along side me before taking the lead and staring off towards the ocean. Ozzy is off to places I cannot follow him yet.  He is no longer in any pain and he belongs to the universe now. And I hope he's on a grand adventure.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/8TIkItj</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Paperhatguy]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>sawdust session</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/6DmTROH</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/fGnXxAU.gif" style